post_text:
The Pinkerton Academy Hotline is a confidential way for anyone to report information about situations that may impact school or student safety. The number can be called any time, day or night, to report concerns about a potentially unsafe situation or a disruptive activity such as drug or alcohol use, bullying, harassment, or threats. All calls will be carefully investigated and remain completely confidential.

The Pinkerton Academy Hotline may be reached by dialing 437-5200, ext. 4444. In an emergency, call 911 immediately.

PA Players
June 10 at 7:28 PM ·

That’s right... it’s Justin Willman giving us just a taste of what will be in store for the 2020-2021 Pinkerton Players show season! If you haven’t heard already, here’s our lineup!

Starting off the year strong, we will be performing ‘Puffs: Live’ a Harry Potter-inspired play! 🧙‍♀️🧙🧙‍♂️🦉
http://www.puffstheplay.com/

Following up is our winter production, ‘Illusion’! 🕵️‍♀️🤵
https://www.broadwayplaypub.com/the-plays/the-illusion/

Last, (but most CERTAINLY not least) we will be concluding the season with our spring musical, Rogers and Hammerstein’s ‘Cinderella’! 💃👗👠

We cannot wait for us to come back together and put on a very exciting and ✨magical✨ season!

#togetherwearepinkerton #artsconnectnh

post_text:
This year's senior officers wanted to find as many ways as possible to celebrate their classmates. They created a special Instagram account that featured profiles of any senior who submitted information up until 5/11. This was shared through the class's social media as well as Pinkerton's Twitter, Instagram, and Facebook pages. They posted multiple times to make sure they hadn't missed anyone who submitted or made any errors in their posts. This video, made by the officers, is a compilation of those profiles.

This is not the revised Senior Slideshow being completed by Mr. Lemire. That will be shared after graduation.

Thank you to the senior class officers for your extra efforts to celebrate your classmates!

PA Players
June 5 at 8:57 PM ·

🎉 CONGRATULATIONS 2020 GRADUATES!! 🎉

We want to take a moment to congratulate our seniors and welcome our incoming eighth graders. You are an inspiration to all of us! You have persevered through the end of its year despite all you have missed, and we are proud of you.
To our seniors- thank you for being a part of Pinkerton Players. We are honored to have been able to be a place for you to explore your interests and share your love of theatre.
To our incoming eighth graders- we cannot wait for you to join us in our upcoming seasons!

So, congratulations to our 2020 graduates, and thank you for all you have done ❤️

#togetherwearepinkerton #artsconnectnh

shared_text:
PA Players
May 22 at 7:01 PM ·

“And now it’s time for the worm himself, Mr. Adam Furgal! Adam has been a dedicated member of the PA Players since his freshman year. He has performed in plays and musicals and served as an officer. The one word I would use to describe Adam (other than “worm”) is FRIEND. So many people across campus call Adam their FRIEND. He has been the glue holding together so many friend groups in our club. Adam is a generous person who so many people turn to when they need a shoulder to cry on, a bit of advice, or a good laugh. In so many ways, Adam has been integral to the identity of our club over the past four years. His friendly face for new members and super polite way of dealing with adults has elevated our club’s profile across the whole campus. It’s hard to imagine the PA Players without Adam Furgal. Those are some big (tap) shoes to fill!”
- Matt Cahoon

Here’s senior Adam Furgal singing “Move On” from the musical Sunday in the Park with George!

#paplayersshowcase #togetherwearepinkerton #artsconnectNH

shared_text:
PA Players
May 15 at 9:04 PM ·

“This one makes me very sad. Eliz Herron is the last of a long line of Herrons who have come through the arts program at Pinkerton and each and every one of them have excelled. When I think of Eliz, the word that comes to mind is JOY. If you have met her, you know that she just has a real love of life and spreads joy throughout the 1R hallway (and probably everywhere else on campus). I will so miss hearing the Herron laugh and the inevitable laughter that came from her friends after she laughed about something. Eliz is a loyal friend and a real lover of music and theatre. It’s hard to imagine what my days will be like without Eliz popping into my office with a huge smile and slightly mischievous look in her eye. I know that she will spread JOY all over campus at Xavier and then bring it to her future patients.”

-Matt Cahoon, Club Advisor

Before you settle down on this nice Friday night, give a listen to Elizabeth’s (PA Class of 2020) beautiful voice singing “I Dreamed a Dream” from Les Miserables.

#paplayersshowcase #togetherwearepinkerton #artsconnectNH

Stockbridge Theatre
April 28 at 10:00 AM ·

Introducing the brand new Virtual Stockbridge Theatre!

While it may be some time before we can welcome patrons back to the Stockbridge in person, we are so pleased to bring you this new online gathering place packed with amazing content provided by our students, faculty, and community. Just find the distinctive red "Launchpads" to Find, Create, and Appreciate! We will be posting new prompts regularly so the content will be constantly changing and updating. Check it out! 🌟 We’d also like to give a shout out and huge thanks to Aspect Virtual for creating the walk through a few years back!
